</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[188,1398,1732,1830]" pageId="7" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName box="[189,443,1732,1758]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sobolifera" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,443,1732,1758]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="79">Euphorbia sobolifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[455,548,1732,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="79" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is only known from a single locality (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1086,1732,1758]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[207,1386,650,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-108@4.[189,1398,632,1890]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Geographical distribution ofEuphorbia blepharadena O.L.M.Silva &amp; Cordeiro sp. nov. (triangle), E. longipedunculata O.L.M.Silva &amp; Riina sp. nov. (star) and E. sobolifera O.L.M.Silva &amp; P.J.Braun sp. nov. (square)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5706228" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5706228/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="79">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), with AOO &lt;
<quantity box="[1261,1337,1732,1760]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="79" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
² and EOO &lt;
<quantity box="[276,367,1768,1796]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="79" unit="km" value="100.0">100 km</quantity>
², and its habitat is subjected to continuing decline in area, extent and quality. We suggest that it should be classified as Critically Endangered (CR; B2ab[iii]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
